FBIS3-39955 "drweu037_k_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 PORTUGAL Deputy Parliament Speaker Resigns LD1902183594 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 1800 GMT 19 Feb 94 LD1902183594 Lisbon Radio Renascenca Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Leonor Beleza could not resist the political and personal pressure that has now led her to hand in her resignation as deputy speaker of parliament and member of parliament. Prime Minister Cavaco Silva and Parliament Speaker Barbosa de Melo have already received the resignation. Beleza argues that, despite proof that she has no civil or criminal responsibility for irregularities when she was health minister, she is not willing to continue with a sacrifice she considers disproportionate. [passage omitted]
